daily_routine: Each morning Elena would check the traditional calendar her grandmother
  kept, marking the days when families should begin preparing for seasonal moves north
  to follow agricultural work. She maintained a small milkweed garden where she taught
  local children about monarch lifecycles, but fewer children came each year as families
  abandoned the traditional patterns. She spent afternoons at the community radio
  station, broadcasting weather and crop information to scattered family networks,
  trying to coordinate movements that no longer followed the old rhythms.
