final_thought: The monarchs and her people followed the same invisible highways for
  so long - both now lost because the world changed too fast for memory to bridge
  the gap.
last_days_scenario: Elena sits in her empty house during what should have been departure
  week, holding her grandmother's cloth map. The milkweed in her garden has been contaminated
  by drift from the new soy plantation next door - the same neonicotinoids that killed
  the last monarchs. Her radio broadcasts reach no one; the families have scattered
  to cities or been deported. She traces the old routes with her finger, knowing that
  like the monarchs, her people's ancient pattern of movement has been broken. The
  knowledge that took six generations to accumulate died in one summer when her grandmother
  couldn't survive the heat and Elena couldn't cross the border to learn the final
  pieces of their family's migration wisdom.
